  <description type="morphology">Subshrubs, 15–35 cm. Stems branched mostly in proximal 3/4, puberulent to coarsely stipitate-glandular. Leaves: blades linear-oblong to linear-lanceolate, (2–)2.5–5 mm wide, bases truncate or rounded-auriculate, margins flat, usually entire, rarely few-toothed, faces puberulent to coarsely stipitate-glandular. Peduncles 3–11 cm. Involucres 10–17 × 15–30 mm. Ray florets 13–21; corollas light blue to white. Style-branch appendages slightly shorter to ± equaling stigmatic lines. 2n = 12, 24.</description>
